entries.femaleVariant: Connect here.
How should I connect? Personal link?
How else? Just watch the jack. Sometimes you have to jiggle it a bit.
[Jack in] Ready.
Now, that wasn't so bad, was it?
Shit. It keeps giving me an error. Odd. Let me work around it.
Just some malware.
Nothing to worry about.
It's not a virus. Just a little malware. You get used to it eventually.
I know, but it's nothing to worry about. Nothing dangerous or anything.
Maybe for you. But this vehicle only has basic security soft. If it's something advanced...
Uh-huh. Just wondering how it'll work with moving targets.
Wonder how it would work with moving targets.
Don't worry. Nothing too advanced. Pretty backwards, actually.
How do I connect?
The connection is secure.
Uh, I've got a bioprocessor in my head that operates independently of me. Probably why your diagnostics flagged it.
Your software could use an update.
Calibration's fine, but your soft could really use an update. Scanner, controllers – all a couple generations back, at least.
But no data will leak out of it through the personal link. Your ride's secure.
Fine. I trust you won't fuck anything up.
Hold on tight. This could get a little bumpy.
OK. Here goes nothing.
Hey, if you'd rather daydream, please wait until we're done calibrating.
We need to calibrate you with the turret.
I want you to be able to use the gun, too. It should up our chances in general.
V? You going to connect?
Is this really necessary?
Wait a moment. Diagnostics first.
Hey, uh, I think your implant has a virus. The one in the nape of your neck.
And now, Panam, here's Johnny! Out in the middle of bumfuck nowhere. Great work, V.
Mhm. OK...
Where's the power station?
So where's this power station?
The gun is calibrated. You'll have system support. Just be careful with the recoil, it sometimes knocks things out of balance.
You will see in a moment.
Do we really have to waste our time on this?
We do.
Unless you've already used one of these without help, while moving, while taking fire from all directions. And still managed to hit something.
But somehow, I don't believe that's the case. So don't argue, just connect.
You see that pile of junk? Fire a short burst into it. I'll take care of the calibration.
Good. Next target. Single shot.
OK. Just one more. Longer round.
Great. We're done, I think.
Each antenna collects microwave energy from satellites in orbit. That's then converted into electric power.
Screw you.
Will it affect the calibration?
We shall see.
Real fucking funny.
You had better see a ripperdoc after all this is over.
All right, mom.
Done anything like this before?
There's better tech in the bargain bin at a Kabuki flea market. I can help you with that, you know.
Yes, sure. The most important thing is that it works now.
I know a spot. We'll have a decent view from there.
Who owns this power station? Gov or corp?
Is there any difference? Who do you think pulls the government's strings?
I'm just wondering whose toes we're about to step all over.
entries.maleVariant: Hey, I'm just wondering whose toes we're about to step all over.

entries.femaleVariant: V, look around. It is simple. Everything you see is owned by a corporation.
'Cause me, I had to carry a real 'ganic iguana once.
Seriously? A live one?
Yup. Someone put 'im in a deep sleep, packed 'im in a cooler. No idea why, but man, I made a shitload off that job. Your turn – think you can beat that?
The deputy finance director of Kaukaz.
Whoa. I'd say it's a tie.
Dead. In the trunk.
OK, fine, you win.
What, are we playing twenty questions?
C'mon, answer.
The deputy finance director of Kaukaz.
That's chauffeuring, not smuggling.
He rode in the trunk. Flatlined.
Really? Dead?
A long story. Maybe someday I'll tell you.
Subject change! What's the weirdest thing you've ever smuggled?
And you like to mess with the corps, huh?
You like to mess with the corps, huh?
Whatever gave you that idea?
Or wait, scratch that.
Well, then I suppose it's a good thing I'm on your side, isn't it?
Rogue, Nash, the Raffens...
Mhmmm.
And now for something completely different. Weirdest thing you've ever transported – go.
You're on thin ice, V.
You just like to mess with everyone.
[Lean out] That's a lotta antennas. How do we choose the right one?
[Lean out] So we set off a chain reaction.
This power station serves the whole city?
Power station serve the whole city?
Honestly? Who the fuck knows.
Guess we're about to find out.
Huh, antennas run all the way down the interstate…
Mhm. And they're linked, which is to your advantage. We just need to mess with the collection unit. A chain reaction will follow. Each one of the antennas will emit an EMP burst.
The AV will be like a fly headed for a spider's web. We just have to fire off the pulse at the right moment.
Let's go get 'er.
Antennas run a ways down the interstate. We set off a chain reaction that starts in the collection unit…
...then each antenna will emit a massive EMP burst.
While our AV flies right into our net.
Let's go get 'er.
We just have to send out the pulse at the right moment.
Downing an AV? By myself? No.
Why do you ask?
'Cause you put together one helluva plan.
Rogue was right. You are good at this game.
You never did anything like this with the Aldecaldos?
Power station, EMP, the systems, networks... Came up with a really solid plan.
Seems Rogue was right.
Thought you woulda done something like this with your clan.
Thank you.
How you approach things – that's the trick. Mine is the triple A.
What now?
Assessment, Assembly, Action.
Whatever your task, you do three things. Start by assessing what you already have and what you'll face, the problem.
Then you plan with those variables in mind. Take what you have, get what you need, assemble things, people. Finally, you take action. Simple.
What? She said you were good. And she was right.
Yes. I suppose she was.
But we have yet to take the AV. So you might wait before you fasten a halo on her.
Know what? Think I figured you out.
Fuck off. I will get both done.
Oh, you have, have you?
Either pull off this mission or prove Rogue wrong – choose one.
No... We did take back one of ours from a convoy once. But this, what we're doing now...
The risk is so much greater.
You don't miss it?
What? Jobs like this?
Being in a clan. Being part of a family.
I could ask you the same. How do you feel, all on your own?
Didn't answer my question.
Not sure. Still think about it sometimes.
I don't miss a thing.
Hey, now. Didn't answer the question.
Yeah, sometimes wonder what life would be like, back with the clan.
No. That chapter's closed.
Because I have no answer to give. Yet.
And?
And the price is always too damn high.
OK. We'll be there in a moment.
Hmm. I believe I understand.
Besides, I try not to regret what's already decided. Just a time sink, usually.
I wish I could let bygones be bygones. Like you.
Get ready!
Sabotage a corpo power station, jump a corpo transport, kidnap a corpo suit…
This a plug for the word corpo or do you have a point?
Know what? You're starting to remind me of me... fifty years back.
Hm. Maybe we CAN just get along.
It's not about the corpos. It's about survival.
[Wait] What do we do now?
Let me remind you, I want Hellman for me, not to stick it to Arasaka.
So, what now?
We wait. We should time our arrival to the AV flight plan.
This is life or death. MY life or death.
Um, and let me remind YOU that 'Saka and their fucked-up tech is what got you here.
Who gives a shit about motives? Ends justify the means. And right now, your end is to survive.
Maybe we really are alike.
Could be something to that, I suppose…
You're more like me than you think. You'll see.
What happened to us, it must've had some effect.
But it goes both ways. Maybe you're becoming more like me.
Nah, no way.
Got it.
"Overload the systems?" Sounds like my kind of job.
Can't we just blow it up?
Panam, what if we cut all the cute stuff and blow the station up?
Normally, I'd love to. But an explosion would trigger an automatic shutdown protocol in each collector.
All Night City would know we were there well before we got around the protocol. Nice idea, though. Maybe next time.
"Overload the system." Yes, ma'am – when do I start?
It shouldn't be. You just turn everything up as far as it'll go.
Crank it up to eleven. Got it.
Why don't I start with the transformers, make mayhem in the relative voltages? Rest should move faster after that.
Not a bad idea. It's just…
Yeah, yeah, I know, the converters… But they shouldn't be a problem. I'll just crank everything up past max.
Seems we think alike!
Once we reach the station, I'll set up a bypass for the detonator. You just overload the systems.
When we arrive at the station, you overload the systems. I'll set up a bypass link for the detonator.
What if something goes ass up?
Triple A – you make that up?
What if, uh, something goes ass up?
Hah, not at all... I learned it from the Aldecaldos. Mitch and Scorpion.
They were trained in something like it during the war. Then they made it their own. It's come in handy, I can't deny. And it will again now.
Well, then your ass had better improvise. Did you really think I'd just give you a foolproof secret to success?
Gotta say, almost had me believing just that.
You're too much sometimes, V.
Your method, Triple A – that all you?
Good, time to roll.
One last time – we drive in, fuck up the system and get the hell out of there.
OK. I'm ready.
We've almost reached the dam. We'll make a quick stop here.
The huge thing is the collection unit. And see the antennas?
Triple A – it's all you need to lead the good life. That and the occasional cold beer.
Got one word for you – T-shirts.
Although... hopin' that's not too complicated. Is it?
entries.maleVariant: Though... hopin' that's not too complicated. Is it?

entries.femaleVariant: Minus the charisma... and impressive cock.
Wired in.
"Overload the systems?" Sounds like my kind of job.
I'll kick the transformers out of whack. Things'll go faster.
[Jack in]
All looks clear. The area looks deserted, I see no patrols.
I just want to be sure the area is clear.
Uh, V?
